<link href="adcp.css" rel="stylesheet"><entry><xh5> hard-headed • soft-headed</xh5><p> <i>hard-headed—</i>1. rational and shrewd, not influenced by sentiments: She was <u>hard-headed</u> enough to be practical about the situation. 2. self-willed and obstinate: I was so <u>hardheaded</u>, I wouldn’t admit to being wrong even if I was at gunpoint.</p><p> <i>soft-headed</i>—(coll.) foolish: Saying that someone else is <u>softheaded</u> is no way to convince people of anything.</p> </entry>
